<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-01T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-01T21:00:00-05:00" n="321" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d321">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">800.91293/19: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-01T22:00:00-04:00">April 1,
                                1944—10 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>421. Department has brought the problem mentioned in your 556, March 30, 11
                        a.m. to the attention of the Washington bureau of the Associated Press,
                        which will refer it to New York. Your part in this matter has been duly
                        safeguarded. You will be informed of further developments when they are
                        known.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>